## Answer:

**rs34574566 (in BRCA2) is the strongest candidate associated with both male breast cancer and breast carcinoma.**  While other variants may have some association with breast cancer, BRCA2 mutations are well-established high-penetrance risk factors for both male and female breast cancer.
